caption: Frankly my favorite bagel shop in town! While I spent a little more for the lox bagel, the size of the bagel and fillings was generous, making up for the price - a worthwhile investment. Lines can be long in the mornings (especially weekends) but with a little patience you'll be well rewarded. Parking may be tricky at times but be sure to follow the signs to park past the rock gym or find parking in the main downtown area.
The tofu cream cheese is amazing. Tastes just like cream cheese.
Yummy but can you make a dozen bagels option !

You've got one of two choices to make here. If you want the run of the mill bagel, then go get yourself the run of the mill bagel.  You've got a handful of  other bagel options throughout Gainesville. If you want the BEST, the BIGGEST, the most FLAVORFUL, the most ORIGINAL NYC tasting, and the most options for your bagel, then you'll need to head on over to Luke's to experience what a real bagel taste like. For those of you that want to complain about having to wait "longer" in line than anywhere else, well, all I can say to that is go somewhere else.  This isn't fast food/drive thru, it's quality bagels done the right way.   Where else are you going to go and get original cream cheese flavors made in house, like pumpkin spice during Halloween or apple pie crust cream cheese, or cinnamon spice bagels.  Or that amazing Asiago Bacon bagel.  Come on, man!   Luke's has the best bagels in the county and proof of that is in how often they are sold out before 1pm closing time. Luke's staff works very hard at what they do and do their very best in providing the community with a top notch quality product at what is a very reasonable price, especially for a bagel sandwich.   Go price breakfast sandwiches elsewhere and you'll see that Luke's isn't off the mark.  Again, for those of you griping about the wait...get outta line and go elsewhere so I can get my bagel order faster :) As a New Yorker, Luke's has the best bagel, best cream cheese, and best hot sandwiches and I'd wait twice as long if necessary in order to sink my teeth into one of his bagels. Take a minute to meet Luke and his dad Mike and the rest of the staff.   These guys are the real deal.   Keep up the GREAT WORK, guys.

Luke's is one of the top three breakfasts in Gainesville without question. Even when the line is around the corner 10 minutes after opening I stop by because I know it's well worth the insane wait. People stop me all the time at work to ask where I got my bagels from because they just look so delicious; we've recommended Luke's to tons of our friends and now we spot them in line all the time! Sure the love is a little cultish but just try their bagels once and you'll understand why

Definitely worth whatever the wait time is, especially since they added sandwiches (and the hash browns 🤤🤤🤤). Service has always been great and everyone is so friendly. One of my favorite places in town!

So so so worth it. Grab a coffee downtown, then head to Luke's with a friend for a nice conversation while you wait for a delicious bagel. Then head to depot park to enjoy it with the sun. A weekend plan you won't regret!

My husband and I were driving around Gainesville on a Saturday morning and we randomly saw the line to Luke's bagels. We graduated UF around 2014 so we had never heard of Luke's, but after seeing that line, we KNEW we had to check it out. (gotta stay young, you know haha) The line went by pretty fast and we ordered lox sandwiches with the orange and blue bagels (in true Gator fashion). It was DELICIOUS! The salmon, cream cheese, capers, etc. were all so well made! It completely made our Saturday morning. These college students are BLESSED to have this in Gainesville! Photo from @foodpeopleluv on IG
My absolute favorite bagels ever. I have Luke’s at least once a week and it’s always the highlight of my day. 10/10 love this place

Spectacularly good bagels.  These folks do it right, from the bagels & bagel sandwiches to the delicious cream cheeses.  Service is very friendly and pretty fast...they just are THAT BUSY.  When you find a real foodie destination, the line is a part of the experience, so be prepared for a significant wait if you arrive after 8am.  One of Gainesville’s true gems!
These bagels are the best bagels I’ve ever had. No matter how long the line is it’s worth the wait.
Amazing bagels!! Definitely worth checking out Luke's!

Closest thing to New York Bagels I've had outside of New York, and best bagels in Gainesville. 100% worth the wait, and the wait isn't that long, especially if you get there at a reasonable time and not when there's a rush. It's not a fast food restaurant, these are quality bagels with accurate and delicious flavor and texture. Don't be lazy - wait in line! Unless you don't want good bagels 🤷‍♀️

Luke's is such an incredible small business that has been extremely successful especially during this pandemic. Yes, the waits are long but I PROMISE you they are worth it! They even play music to try to make your wait more enjoyable! Their selection is expansive as well but I prefer to try their "bagel of the day" (rainbow sunday and chocolate chip are my favorite). If you truly are too busy to wait in line, GO EARLY!!!! OR you can take advantage of their call ahead ordering on tuesdays and wednesdays! If you haven't given this amazing business a try simply because the waits are too long, SHAME on you. Every bagel is homemade and DEFINITELY worth waking up at 6 am on the weekend!!!
Best bagels in Florida hands down! I'm originally from New Jersey and thoroughly enjoyed the Taylor ham, egg, and cheese on a jalapeño cheddar bagel. I'll be visiting whenever I'm in Gainesville!

Small, locally owned business. Don't expect to be in and out quickly. That's not how small, locally businesses work (except early on a Tuesday when you can call in your order😜). Best bagels I've ever had. The lox sandwich is SO delicious. Their breakfast sandwiches are on another level. I would give ten stars if I could.

Luke's has the best bagels I have ever had. If you haven't tried them, you definitely need to. It may ruin every other bagel you try to eat after because no bagel will ever compare, but they are definitely worth the wait in line. The Pork roll Bagel sandwiches are unlike anything I have ever had. I eat mine on the egg everything and they have dairy-free crème cheese options for people like me who are afraid of dairy. The price is super fair for how big they are and how fresh they are (they make fresh ones every night). You won't be disappointed.
This place is AMAZING. Any bad reviews must be from people who’ve had COVID and lost their tastebuds.

Beyond excellent. Your taste buds will rejoice after experiencing the amazement that is produced by this place. So good you may take a bite and want to get back in line.  Only complaint is it will ruin all other bagel shops because this place is #1.

Listen!!! You cannot sleep on Lukes Bagels! Okay? Your going to wait in line but anything that is this good is worth the wait! You might need to wake up a little earlier but then you have all that extra time for adventures!!! Get yourself a Pork Roll egg and Cheese or a Bacon Egg and Cheese!
Best bagels in town. Tuesday-Thursdays would definitely recommend calling ahead and picking up. It’s definitely worth the 15-30 minute wait on the other days. Really nice staff and spectacular food.

Best bagels in all of Gainesville! Definitely worth the wait if there is one. We moved away from Gainesville and I seriously think about these bagels all the time and wish they were everywhere. Excellent staff!

Best bagels I've ever tried. Super light and moist on the inside and soft yet nice crust on edge. Ordered a whole bag of bagels and froze some to eat all week. If you are an early bird, the line was short when they opened! I first got the bagels in the height of Covid and they made the weekend oh so much better. Small shop of hard working nice people! Thanks Luke for bringing this awesome shop to us!

As a student, I came here all the time and loved supporting a fellow gator. I used to travel to NYC often and was always on the quest for a great bagel. These are the best I’ve ever had anywhere. The egg everything 🥰 If you want to beat the crowd, come on a slow day like Tuesday or go right when they open at 7am any day they’re open.
Since my first visit there, Luke’s has become my favorite spot in Gainesville! They have so many different options and they are all delicious. Best bagel place I’ve been to in Florida!
Loved their sesame bagel with tofu veggie cream cheese! Worth the wait.
Best bagel shop in Florida - absolutely recommend stopping by if you’re in Gainesville. Come early because the line gets super long!
Worth the wait and definitely exceeds expectations! Best bagels in Gainesville!
Excellent bagels. Show up early.

Luke’s is by far the best bagel I’ve ever had! I was born and raised in southern New Jersey so I know what a real bagel tastes like and Luke’s is unmatched. I’ve been going there since opening day and could not have been happier to ditch the supermarket bought bagels for my weekly supply of Luke’s. When they finally started selling breakfast sandwiches I was in heaven. Pork Roll, Egg, & Cheese till I die! If you don’t get Luke’s you’re missing out

There's been a gap in bagel/deli quality in Gainesville for a few years since Bagels Unlimited moved from midtown further west. Luke's absolutely fills and exceeds that void. Delicious. Easy call-ahead ordering during the week (at time of review, maybe that will expand). Looking forward to post-Covid conditions so I can frequent Luke's with extreme frequency, but will definitely stop by as often as possible in the meantime. Thanks, Luke's!
Best breakfast in Gainesville, hands down!! I go every chance I get! Worth the wait! Their instagram is super helpful for wait times and last minute deals, too!

I love Luke’s bagels! These are the most authentic bagels you can get outside of New York or New Jersey, hands down! Every bagel and spread I have tried has been great (definitely recommend getting them toasted there, unless you have big toaster at home).  Be prepared, there can be quite a line. The location is small and they do the best they can with what they have. I think it’s definitely worth the wait!

Even though you will probably have to wait at least a little bit to get your bagel, the wait is 100% worth it! I have been to Luke’s plenty of times, and I never been disappointed with any of the bagels I have ordered at Luke’s. They have some of the best bagels in Florida, and the prices are decent too! My favorites are the french toast bagel, and a plain bagel with their homemade chive and onion cream cheese.There is a good variety of bagels and spreads, and you can also order breakfast sandwiches, too. The staff is very kind and prompt. Wake up early and check out this local business ASAP!
Amazing bagels, make for a great start to the day.
Best bagels in town!
Luke’s is TOTALLY worth the wait. I never leave disappointed and always look forward to my next visit. If you haven’t already, give them a try!
Fabulous New York bagels. Hot sandwiches take time, but everything else comes out quick. Line up early!!
Really yummy vegan veggie cream cheese! Nothing like I’ve had before
test: 5star reviews
5 star bagels, 3 star service. Been twice, yet to receive everything I’ve paid for. Even if it’s the $0.75 item.
if your looking for a ny style bagel you won’t find it in florida. if you want ny go to NEWYORK. wait is long a little pricey should think about selling iced tea. 3 stars because it wasn’t bad.
Awesome breakfast sandwich
LOVE THIS . Fresh, worth the wait. I go every week
Bagel sandwich was tasty
By far the best bagel joint in FL! Lives up to the name.

Oof. TLDR: Overpriced, flavorless, hard, dry bagels you have to wait ages for. Decided to check them out finally as I'd heard hype and they had a relatively short line. I was so excited. Everyone was nice but sadly that is the only positive. I order two lox sandwiches, one on egg everything and the other on garlic, and another two bagels. The sandwich starts at close to $9PLUS The bagel plus the cream cheese...ok my bad for not seeing the fine print. I also ordered a coffee with cream, I was charged 15 cents extra for creamer? Umm ok. Well I'm hoping $35 in for this it should be good. I take a bite of the egg everything lox sandwich and WOW it's so mediocre I could've cried, day ruined. Bagel was dry, hard, flavorless despite the insane amount of everything seasoning and so chewy it hurt to chew(also untoasted despite me asking for toasted). The garlic bagel was slightly better, didn't feel like I was eating something forgotten in the back of the fridge for a week, but still no flavor and not a NY bagel at all, still super chewy/gummy and slightly dry. In the end I couldn't eat the extra bagels at all, and I picked the lox out of the sandwich to eat. Maybe this was a fluke due to them newly switching systems? Maybe I got a bunch of day old bagels? But I honestly doubt it, the flavor was intensely lacking and I just can't see these getting better. Intensely sad and disappointed and really wishing I hadn't blown money on this place. I'd give it one star if not for the nice server.
Very busy with a great product.
On a foggy Sunday I visited Bagels were mind blowing,, it’s worth waiting long for them 👍👌👌
The best bagels I have ever had!

I went in the early afternoon right before closing for BOGO bagels and only had two people ahead of me in line. The bagels are huge and taste AMAZING. I ate a bacon asiago in my car untoasted with no cream cheese or anything. It was that good. The only thing I don't like is the lack of parking!

1st time was OK, a bit of a wait, but 2nd time, my daughter waited 80 minutes (yes, 1 hour and 20 minutes) for two bagels. I reached out to them via Facebook about it-they were unapologetic and just noted that they had posted about the wait on Fb and Insta (apparently it's the customer's responsibility to monitor that?) and that they had a large volume of customers.  I hope that they can figure out a better system to fulfill demand.  Not going back.

The line moves way to slowly. I’ve been there twice with other people and it will literally take them a solid hour to take 10 peoples order.  Both times I was there it really did take over a hour to order with 10 to 12 people ahead of me.
Food is 5 star. Wait not so much.
Absolutely delicious freshly made bagels and cream cheese.

Always great service and great bagels! Gville definitely needed a place like this. You can tell they're really working hard in there to get you your food as quickly as possible and it's impressive the operation they've put together in such a small place. Worth the hype

From Brooklyn NY originally so we know what a good bagel is. I know this place gets great reviews but our batch was not great. Very long wait times with people who ordered after us getting their food first. We ordered a dozen mixed bagels and an additional five to eat right away and the total was over $50. Nothing great here in service, prices and taste.
Decent bagels, a little pricey though.
Best bagels in town. The only issue is that there is a decent wait to get the bagels since it can get busy.

Great, delicious bagels and the egg everything is the best. The staff is friendly and although the bagels are a bit pricey they are huge and generally worth it. I will upgrade to 5 stars if they (1) come up with a way to get me a couple bagels in a bag right out of the bin without waiting for orders being “prepared” with extras and (2) stop charging sales tax on “just bagels” in a bag, since they are not taxable when not otherwise prepared and are for consumption off premises (see Panera, Bageland).

For 20 years I worked in Manhattan and on my walk to my office I would stop in and buy a bagel from the largest bagel wholesale/retail supplier in Manhattan. It was the center of the universe for bagels. They probably sold 50,000 a day. I know bagels and I am  happy to see so does Luke.

Fantastic bagels overshadowed by awful operations.  The wait time is terrible (and I feel like I'm not asking much for bagels), customer service is kinda lacking, and they have a skip the line program apparently? Lines are huge, but somehow some people can skip and it's really not a good look when some people have been waiting for 20 minutes.  These problems are all fixable and im glad to come back when they're solved. Until then, Luke's is a pass for me.
Can't speak to the bagels, I'm sure they are delicious, but the staff weren't wearing masks at all nor did they ask the customers to wear them. Kind of gross,  so no thanks to this covid crockpot.

this place had a lot of hype, but it didn’t really do it for me. today was my first time and i was expecting it to be like most other bagels shops i’ve been to. even if i got a bagel to-go, they would still cut the bagel at least. the flavor itself was dang good for the everything bagel (i asked for chive cream cheese but they gave me plain. they did spell my name right though!!), but it was handed to me cold, uncut, with the cream cheese on the side, and a flimsy plastic knife i had to cut in my car with(cue the bagel seasoning flying everywhere). i know, i know this is a very Karen review and please roast me endlessly about that, but dog...ya’ll really don’t even cut the bagel lol?
best bagels in town. period.
This is by far the best bagel shop in Gainesville and near by areas! The staff are amazing it's a family business and they rock!  My favorite is the Lox 🥯

Excellent bagels. Worth the price in my opinion. Everything bagels are absolutely loaded, which I am a huge fan of. Some interesting choices like bacon asiago and jalapeno cheddar that I'll have to try next time.
I got the rainbow bagel with tofu cream cheese (vegan) and it did NOT disappoint!!! The prices are great even though they have “fancy” bagels. I would 10/10 recommend Luke’s :)
Best bagels in town!
The best bagels around!
So I grew up in Long Island and let me just say, these bagels SLAP. So glad I found this shop!
This place is legit. And they have lox!

Best bagel place in town. I love the French toast bagel with strawberry cream cheese. I would say the earlier you go the better since the line can be long. Also the plain bagel is really good! I highly recommend
Delicious...waiting in line 10 minutes was worth it....
Only place that I have seen in years that makes egg bagels! Been coming back at least once a month to try their new flavours of bagels and shmear
Delicious and fresh bagels!!! We love them!!

Delicious bagels! I love the texture. Nice crusty outside and good chewy inside. They can be a bit uneven, not sure if they intentionally allow that to show that they are handmade or what. But the cooking is always spot on. I love their everything flavor and I love trying their specials.
service is good and there r so many bagels options also u can add cream cheese and vegetables to it! egg bagel and cinnamon bagel r my favorites!
Absolutely delicious bagels and such a great team. Luke and his team produce bagels that remind me of being back home in Queens. Everyone needs to try these bagels ASAP!
Will fight anyone who doesn't give Luke's 5 stars. Awesome bagels, awesome service! Thank you

I love their bagels! They have a wide variety of bagels which you don't see too often in town, and especially the most from main street to the east side of town. The new york water filter they have brings that NY quality to the bagels. All other place's bagels are inferior now! They ran a poll recently and added even more delicious flavors of bagels and cream cheese! Cheap delicious bagels? Yes please!
Great bagels, and the times I've visited always a line...which speaks to the quality...the bagels are large, not supermarket sized.
Almost sold out so maybe that effected the bagel we chose. Thought it was OK but large and not the combo of chewy on the outside and doughy inside. Hmmm...
Get ready to wait outside for 45 minutes but the food is incredible and well priced
As a native New-Jersian I can say these are the only bagels ive had this good in apl of Florida!

Worth the wait! At 9am we stood 20 min in line and 10 min waiting for our food but the bagels were so crispy on the outside and fluffy doughy on the inside. The lox on egg everything bagel w onion chive cream cheese is my favorite! The French toast bagel with maple walnut smear was amazing (bottom left). Asiago bacon was good as well (bottom right). They were sold out on blueberry and chocolate chip bagels when we arrived. The sun dried tomato smear was ok. I preferred the onion and chive. A bigger better cream cheese selection would make this place unstoppable! The long wait can be a deterrent for some but the staff were so nice and friendly we didn’t mind the wait. They would come out periodically to thank us for waiting and announce if any flavors sold out.

Fantastic bagels. I gave 4 stars because they NEED to get quicker at what they're doing. Have a dry erase board outside with a list of the bagels available so people know what they want before getting to the order window. People taking orders need to keep explanations to a minimum. It's hot, and patrons shouldn't be waiting an hour for a bagel when it's not a long line. If you're there with a group, please be decent and order together to save time. Venmo your friends after. I look forward to coming back when this is a well oiled machine. The everything egg bagel was the best I've ever had.
Great bagels. My favorite is egg everything, followed by poppy seeds. They are adding more menu items like bagel sandwiches
Wait was a bit long, but people were nice and wearing their masks. Bagels were huge. Most were pretty tasty.
Their bagels are the best. Authentic NY bagels. The homemade cream cheese is excellent too. Make sure to get there early or call and order ahead of time.
But, 2nd time returning after they ran out. Also over priced compared to other places in town. Would have called to get order correct but no number posted on business page.

1st time visit. Ok here’s the deal. My friend used to own the Lj Pretzels at this location.I was not Disappointed ! Get there early, be prepared to wait. It was raining and there still was a line (9:30 Sunday morning). I wanted a everything bagel they were out already. I did get a poppy and also a Asiago bagel. My wife had a raisin bagel with walnut maple cream cheese spread. The bagels were big crunchy on the outside and fluffy in the middle very light in the stomach. I will be back to try the others. Very happy.
